“You are a human with one life and it is up to you to make it the best life you can.” -Dan Howell

I was about to finally get off Tumblr and start my to do list for the day, but had to log back in just to post this. I have the Momentum extension for Chrome, which replaces every new tab with a personalized page featuring a different inspirational quote and photo every day. And it was really nice to see a familiar name today. 

Thanks, @danielhowell for inspiring all of us to make our lives the best lives we can. And so glad to know you’re alive, living your truth, and using your one life to have a positive impact on others.

summary: I can’t stop thinking about Dan saying that he attempted suicide in his video. I rewatched that part of the video so many times....
body: I can’t stop thinking about Dan saying that he attempted suicide in his video. I rewatched that part of the video so many times. It definitely wasn’t easy to hear. I always find it heartbreaking any time someone is feeling that low. But I am so grateful that he included that part of his story. I have struggled with suicidal thoughts since I was 11 and I have attempted suicide multiple times. After every attempt, I have agonized about how I failed and how I would give anything to just “succeed” at ending my life. The way Dan handled telling that part of his story was so perfect and he really made me feel like one day I will be glad that I failed. I found myself fixating and trying to put together how he was going to do it, but after watching that part of the video one more time I realized how grateful I am that he didn’t include that detail. For someone like me, the worst thing someone can do when discussing suicide is to mention how someone else did it. That does not make me realize how painful it was for them and everyone who knew them, it sticks in my mind so that I see it as an option. I just want to say a big thank you to Dan for including his story with suicide, it was so brave and it really will help so many people.
